values:
I FINALLY got a job!! Yay for me! I'm working at Fun 'n' Stuff with Ashley. We start tomorrow at 11am. 

So I'm still trying to figure out whether or not I want to live in the dorms or at home in the fall...hmmmm...suggestions are appreciated.

Booo summer school starts in 3 weeks, that's way too soon for me.

I gotta get to sleep so I can be well rested for work. Night!

This summer is really boring...I miss when summer was fun and there were no worries.

I'm still looking for a job...I've applied for anything through Snider-Blake specifically Precise Tech. I went up to Aurora Farms on Tuesday with Kristin, Alexis, and Philip to look for a job, I applied at Mikasa, New England Homes, Welcome Home, and Totes...still waiting to hear back from them. I really need money, I have to pay for my car, insurance, and my crazy ass high cell phone bill this month, plus all kinds of other misc. stuff.

We've come up with this crazy new obsession...4 Sqaure. Remember when back in the day during recess you played 4 Square, well we've brought it back and improved it. Its soooo fun, YOU should come play with us!

Later

So the summer is starting to get a little better

Last weekend I got to see my cousin's baby. She is sooo adorable! I also got paid for watching the dog while they were having the baby.

Monday afternoon Kristin came by and surprised me. I had no idea she was home. I haven't seen here in forever. I guess she is in the process of moving back up here. Yay! I really miss last summer with her, we had some goodtimes. I hope we can make some more awesome memories this summer.

Tuesday I got my license back, but that's not all I got...I got a car too! I bought a 1999 green Plymouth Neon. I've got it all decked out with fun stuff already, thanks to Alexis hehe. I'm so happy.

I'm still waiting for a call for work. They were suppose to call me this week but haven't. I'll have to call on Monday. It's gonna be really interesting going back to work....hmmmm.

Not much else is going on. I'm just glad that my life is starting to get better.

Night!

Summer is rolling by everso slowly...save me somebody.

Congrats Rick and Jen on your new baby girl!
Welcome to the world baby Julie!

I've been dog sitting this week for my cousin while she's in the hospital having her baby. 

Baby Julie was born on May 31 @ 9:50pm, weighing 9 lbs 11 oz.

Time to go finish my cross-stitch...
Bye

This afternoon Penny was outside barking so I went out there to see what was going on. When I got outside, I found her chasing a deer into the woods which she does alot. So I grabbed her to take her into the house before a fight broke out, as I was pulling her I looked back at the deer to make sure he didn't run though the woods and on to Rt.91 and get hit by a car...instead, the deer was running back towards us, which was kinda unusual because they don't usually make any contact with people. Luckily I got into the house before it attacked us. A little while later I noticed that Penny was bleeding from her lip, leg, and front paw. I guess she did get into a fight with the deer before I got outside. I cleaned up all her boo boos like a good vet haha!

A few hours later I heard Penny outside barking again. I went outside and she was barking at this big bush in the corner of our yard. Behind it was a baby deer that had to have been born today, it could barely stand up or walk and it was shaking. My mom sat next to it and tried to feed it, but it was too scared from Penny barking at it. I ran and got my camera, I got some close ups and adorable pics of the newborn before it wandered off to find it's mother. It was sooo cute, it kinda looked like a mini kangaroo, hahaha!!

I guess the mom wasn't really trying to attack us, it was just trying to keep us away from her new baby.
Atleast I get to make fun of Penny for getting her ass kicked by Bambi's mom! lmao!

Quite an eventful day.
It's sleeepytime.

Night!

Hey everyone!

My grandma is in the hospital with pneumonia...but i think she's gonna be alright.

I'm feeling a little relieved. I got alot of my "To Do List" done, just 2 more big things left and then I'm set. What's left is gonna be a bit of a challenge, but I have nothing better to do so I might as well challenge myself a bit.

I finally got all of my grades, 2.5 for the semester and 2.3 cumm...I'm staying at KSU! Woot!

Paid my tuition today for my summer class, I'm out $792. Geez, college is soooo over priced, I'm so in debt.

Being at home is boring as hell, I wish I was at school or working. I gotta get out of the house. I feel like an animal not doing anything.

I don't really have alot else to talk about... 

I'm out, probably off to play some more Mario Kart even though that's all I've been doing the past 3 days straight...someone save me please!

p.s. I miss all my friends that aren't around...call me guys!

Summer is FINALLY here...I guess I'm happy...hmmmm nope not at all

Been sick all week...

got less than 15 hours of sleep all week...

lived on soup, water, and coffee all week...

Finals sucked major ass, now all I can do is pray that I've got a 2.25 for the semester, otherwise I say buhbye.

Tried to sell back my 4 textbooks that cost me $275...they only took 1 book back and gave me $14 for it

Moving out was a pain...as usual (move in, move out, move in, move out geez it's annoying)

Almost got into a car accident with all my stuff in the car because of some Hudson bitch with road rage...

Getting extremely irritated that my grades aren't posted yet...what on earth could they possibly be doing?

Summer isn't gonna be that great either

Gotta get license stuff figured out...

Get a car... or find one to use

Find a job...

Take a class at KSU...

Ehhhh Booooo!

I hate being at home with the family, I just wanna do what I want when I want to.
If I wanna sleep all day or lounge around and watch movies or whatnot, I want to be able to do it without people bothering me and bitchin.

Miss my roomie...(and everybody else.)

Time for bed...gotta wake up at 7am (again, no sleep for the goose)

Love ya!

Yo! Not much happening here...just stuffness, same old.

Can't wait for this semester to be over. 2 weeks of classes + 1 week of finals = 3 weeks till summer!
Not that it really matters to me since I'm going to summer school and working. Woot woot!

I love this song...

Losing You 
by AM 

I saw a road that had no end
I wanted you so I followed it
And what you take is what you should give
But the stories came and the stories went
I gave so much of myself to you
But that's alright, I wanted to
And nothing learned don't know what to do
There's no lesson here, I'm losing you
You wanted nothing we talked about
I thought I had you figured out
I had so much to give you now
I was sure of you, but you had your doubts
Don't you worry, you're not to blame
I've been on your side, playing those games
Now you're just in a different place
There's nothing left, let's walk away

 

Love ya
Adios amigos!

Hi! Hi!

This past weekend I went home to do some stuff. Friday night my mom and I went to Coldstone Creamery, that was yummy, and we rented 2 movies, 'Closer' and 'Open Water'. Closer really really sucked, there wasn't much of a plot. I'm not sure how it won two awards. Open Water was good, but the ending was kinda unclear. 

Then, saturday we went to my cousin's baby shower, always a fun time. Saturday night, my cousin Kevin came up to spend the night up here to see what college life is like. It was really boring because the campus was dead, I have no clue where everybody went but nobody was around. So we just walked around campus and chilled in my room. Sorry it sucked, hopefully next time stuff will be going on and there will be people around.

Next weekend, Candace is coming up here for Lil' Sibs weekend, that should be an interesting time. Hmmm...somebody save me!

I got my income tax returns...$500, Hell Yeah!!

This weather is so fabulous! *Knock on wood*

I have to study my ass off for my art history test now...

Peace out!

Ohio weather really sucks. It shouldn't be raining/sleeting/snowing over spring break. Next week it's suppose to be 60 degrees, why not this week when it's spring break?? Damn you Ohio.

It's nice to be away from my family...across the street, I guess you could call that "away." Geez, then my little sister shows up to bother me...yeah so much for getting away from her. It's kinda pretty boring living in my neighbor's house. It's really hard to get comfortable and find something to do in someone else's house...even though we are like family, it's just weird. I've been playing with their pets, studying for my business test, and watching TV, and just sitting around ponder what I should do to entertain the situation. It's funny how you can have 900 channel and yet still there's nothing to watch, that would be why I hate TV. Craziness...

So I recently became extremely obsessed with Gilmore Girls. I used to see clips of it or whatnot and think that it was a stupid show, so I don't understand my new obsession at all...but I'm addicted!! I love the fast paced and witty conversations they have...but seriously, what 32 yr old mom and 16 yr old daughter talk like that?? I see the mom talking with a big vocab, but not the 16 yr old. I don't think I could ever have such a sophisticated conversation like they do, even if I tried. I need a dictionary with me when I watch it. Ohhh but I really love the show now...so I have to catch up on 5 seasons, since I decided to just tune in, hahaa! I've got quite a few of the episode under my belt already, so I'm making progress. Silly silly me!

This week I got back into watching Days of Our Lives. It's interesting how some of the story lines seem to be in the same place they were when I stopped watching in August. Then, there's others that changed so much that I don't even know who the characters are or what on earth is going on. Geez,I'm finally figuring things out after watching it the past 4 days, but when I get back to school I probably won't watch it, and I'll have to get back on track in May.

That new show "The Office" premiered tonight....funny stuff, it's just like Office Space but 10x better. It's really slow humor, but good. I wonder how it will progress, only so much can happen in an office. OK, enough with TV, cause it sucks! :) Sorry my whole entry turned into TV stuff.

Well that's all for now...
Happy Easter to everyone since I probably won't be able to update for awhile, since my internet at school doesn't work.
Bye for now!

Yo! Long time no talk...sorry guys!

Good ol' Hudson'ville' is falling apart...drunk bus driver, student protesting to save our HS principal, according to the media it was a "RIOT" (riiight), and rumors of violence at school causing 1400 of 1800 students to stay home from school because rumor was students were planning on "hurting themselves or others." WOW! 3 weeks of hell...talk about a great community and school district gone wild. It's rather funny how one news reporter described Hudson, "Quaint shops, polite people, and time passes without a hitch...that's the norm here in Hudson, not (a riot)" I love how they made it sound like fairy tale land, LMAO! HHS students: don't give up fighting for Howard. We DON'T need a new principal, but we DO need a new superintendent. Check our these sites www.weloverogerhoward.com and www.recalltheboard.org.

Also, the next person that I see spell princiPAL wrong on the message board is going to die. That's really sad that you guys are in high school and keep spelling principal(the person), like "pinciPLE"!

So I'm on spring break now. I have absolutely no plans...I'm house/dogs/cats/stuff sitting for Ash! I get to live at their house for a week and entertain their pets, hahaha fun stuff! :D I'm also gonna be study for my Business exam that I have right when I get back from break. Grrr!

I'm so angry right now, I could seriously put my fist through a wall. I signed up for my remedial class, it was suppose to be 9am till 5pm today...but the instructor never showed up...drove all the way out there for nothing. Those people are gonna get a really pissy phone call from me on Monday morning! I'm glad I'm not them when I get done with them.

March 12th was the 2 year anniversary of George Silver's death. I can't believe it, it still feels like yesterday. 
*We all miss and love you Jorge!*

That's it for now! Peace!

Thursday night Alexis came out here to Kent to chill. We hung out in the dorm, drank Jager and watched Napoleon Dynamite. We weren't happy with the buzz we got so Britt, Alexis, Tristan, and I went to DX for a while. We met this really creepy guy who came up to Britt and kept asking her all kinds of questions. He said that he was from Akron and stuff. He was all alone standing in the corner staring at us, and following us around, it was really scary. Who comes out to a Kent party all alone from Akron?? Seriously, who does that?? Britt stayed at the party with Paul, so the rest of us staggered our way back to the dorm. I made my drunken dials while trying not to wet my pants on the walk back. I made some drunken visits around the dorm, then we went to Rosie's to meet up with Moose and Dave...apparently before we left I made some shocking confessions. I don't remember any of it, oops sorry. Alexis and I got back from our rendevous with Moose and company, watched Dirty Dancing and crashed around 5am. Overall, it was a pretty weird night, everybody was really moody...it was odd. There was something weird about it that we couldn't figure out. Atleast I got drunk!!

Friday we woke up around 9:30 when we heard Britt getting ready for class. OMG, I couldn't even function, it was like a zombie/ out of body experience. Finally around 11 Alexis and I physically woke up. She came to sociology with me...blah, I couldn't even follow what my teacher was saying. The overhead wouldn't work so we got let out 30 min early. We then caught the bus to the stadium to pick up Alexis's car, omg the bus was so packed, I've never seen so many people before. There were 4 people on the bus from Hudson, the bratty little freshman. Alexis went home and I went back to sleep..yay!

Saturday night Britt and I went to watch Pat, Paul, Jenna, and Jeanette at Songfest for their Frats/ Sors. It was pretty cool seeing their dances and songs. It lasted 3 1/2 hrs and it was soooo hot in the balcony, we were dying and getting irritated. The stupid girl giving away the raffle ticket prizes kept saying that everything was "fun". Geez... "well this is a FUN little prize" and "that's FUN" and "hope you have FUN" FUN FUN FUN FUN FUN.... God, we were about to strangle her, ditzy brat. There were a bunch of parties afterward but I decided to stay in cuz I was still recovering from Thursday.

Yesterday was Kristin's 20th B-day!! Happy Birthday! Hope you're having an awesome time down in NC. 

Blah blah blah... I have a Child Psych to get ready for tomorrow and an Art History test on thurs...boooo for school

Bye!

Ok ok ok, I'm updating due to people whining (not to mention any names, Britt), I haven't updated because nothing has happened that's worth writing about. So, now I'm gonna try and find current events in my life to entertain you with....hmmmm....

So I've been trying to hang out with Moose but he seems to be really busy or something...or just doesn't like me:( I don't know what the deal is there. I like him, he's cute, nice, sweet! I'm sick of asshole guys, I don't think he could be an asshole even if he tried. Hopefully we can hang out again, we'll see what happens!

Classes are going alright, I've had tests the last few weeks. Art History- C, Soc- B, and Business- C. The past few days I've been studying my ass off for my Child Psych test that was suppose to be today, but when I got to class I found out that she moved it to next week...damn, I was all ready and pumped to take it, oh well looks like I can prep some more.

Last Friday Alexis and I went to lunch at Chipotle. Kristin was home from C-bus so she came with us and brought Bryan too. I love that kid, he's soooooo funny, it's always a fun time with him!! :) It was so awesome getting to see my favorite peeps. Good times, love ya guys so much! Kristin...I'm gonna try and come visit you over spring break, and if I don't, you know why.

I went to the doctor for the cheese that was growing on my tonsil, it ended up being nothing. Well it was something, but nothing to be concerned about and couldn't be cured with meds...I'm glad I paid $20 for him to tell me it was nothing. Anyway, it went away by itself a few days after. Haha it was really gross!

I bought a mini iPod. Oh its fun to play with! :) I was just gonna get an mp3 player but got talked into getting the iPod since it's better and of course more expensive. You should get one, I highly recommend it!

Ok well I'm out...leave some sugar!

Gen

P.S. What did you think of my previous entry? 
Britt...it's about Bob, You should have known that.

Days and months have past since you walked away leaving me all alone
I know that you aren't coming back, still I sit here hoping and waiting
I walk around wearing this fake smile, pretending I don't miss you, when inside it's tearing me apart
I wonder where you are and how you're doing, even though I shouldn't care
And I wonder if you ever think about me
If only I had told you how I felt and showed you how much I loved you
If only you kept your promises and not let me down
If only...
You might still be here today
You said that you had to leave because you didn't want to hurt me
But you hurt me anyway, because goodbye hurt more than anything
You said that we would stay friends, but we haven't spoken since
Now I have nothing left but memories of us
Every night I walk out to where we used to watch the stars, wishing on a star that you'll come back to me
I can't get you out of my mind, no matter how hard I try, I just can't stop thinking about you
I miss your smile...
I miss your laugh...
I miss your pretty blue eyes...
I miss your sweet kisses and warm hugs...
I miss your scent...
I miss talking to you...
I miss everything about you...
But what I miss most is being your friend...
I may have learned how to live without you, but I still miss you more everyday!


*I miss you* :(

Hey hey!
Oh yay for Valentine's day...actually no! I really hate Valentine's Day, I never have a valentine and being single sucks. When we were little Valentine's was so fun, we'd make valentines for our friends and people in our class and it was just a big old party. But now, it's just sad and it makes you realize you are all alone. Anyway, for V-day Moose and I had nothing to do, so we watched movies and hung out...that was my HOT date! HEHE!

I bombed my Child Psych test last week that I stayed up all night studying for...I got a D, I was 1 point away from a C. It's ok though, it was the first test, atleast I know whats to come on the next tests.

Yesterday I had an Art History test...a.k.a the test from hell, but I think at worst I'll get a C, I hope! We'll see tomorrow! The weather yesterday was gorgeous, ya gotta love it when it's the middle of Feb and 60 degrees and sunny out. Then, you wake up the next morning to 30 degrees and an inch of snow. Boy do I love OHIO!

I have a Soc test on Friday, I don't think it's going to be that bad. Today in class we reviewed for the test, and our crazy, red complementing, Croatian, prostitute-like professor gave us all the questions and answers that will be on the test. Who does that? Those silly foreigners, gotta luv 'em! A+ here I come, thanks!

People are really annoying and immature. I honestly hate people in general...I know I sound like a horrible person, but it's true. Sorry! But I love my friends, thanks for putting up with me guys!

Well I'm off to see the______! (use your imagination, insert something funny) Hehe!

Peace out homies!

Happy Thursday...was gonna go out and party it up tonight but I don't think that's happening.

I pulled an all nighter last night studying for my child psych test and I still think I bombed it. So much for all the studying I did. Atleast I got to chill with Kesha all night and then we went to Rosies to get breakfast at 6am, just like old times! I slept maybe 5 hrs today, but I'm still exhausted I won't make it through the night if I go out to D-Chi.

The sore throat that I've had the past couple of days has now turned into laryngitis...just great! I can talk just a teeny bit, but it feels like someone is ripping my throat open when I do.

Tomorrow I'm going home for the weekend, having a little family get together at my g'parents nursing home. Good times!

I'm out...like a "whispering" pine

Later
Gen

Busy busy busy past few days...

Thursday night Tristan, Britt, Paul and I went to Delta Chi. It was sooo much fun, I got totally shit faced...it's been awhile. Britt left early though because she didn't feel well. We all had an awesome time, ran into a bunch of people that I haven't see in awhile...good times. While we were there Tristan found out that one of his residents was killed in a car accident earlier that night along with 2 other students from KSU...it was really sad :( Anyway, it was a good night and I'm really glad I decided to go out, since I never go out. Thanks for everything Paul! :D

Saturday morning I went home for the day to build a bookcase for my sister because my mom insisted it get done  and it couldn't wait till next weekend when I was planning on coming home. It was a blast, ahhhh it took me almost 3 hours. Came back that night did my stupid business stock project and then watched Collateral with Britt, Paul, and Tristan.

Today I went with Britt to the mall so she could buy a dress for Formal, that took all day since she went into every store atleast twice and ended up buying 3 dresses. But it was fun spending time with her, even though I live with her. Haha gotta love her! Tonight I hung out with Charlie, it was good to see him again.

I'm out...gotta watch Desperate Housewives woot!

Gen

Hi to everybody who's still reading this...sorry its been awhile, but not alot has been going on. 

Today is Britt and Paul's one year anniversary...awww yay! I am SO happy for them, they're absolutely adorable. Congrats guys! Love ya!

Tomorrow is my mom's Birthday. Last weekend we went out to dinner at Olive Garden to celebrate. Our waiter was sooooo cute and funny, his name was Brian and he goes to university of akron and is a DJ for WZIP (UofA's radio station) haha it made me think of Paul. Anyway, he was awesome, I liked him alot, and he kept talking to me and joking around and stuff, it was cute. He gave my parents free coffee, hmmm haha! He got a very very nice tip.

Classes are going good. I've got tests in all of them coming up in a week or so. I thought they would be easy classes this semester, but I think I'm gonna have to work a little harder than I thought.

I still need to figure out where I'm living next year...and who I'm going to room with...I really need to get on that before there's nothing left.

Winter makes me lonely. Blahh! I wonder what Bob has been up to and how he's doing??? I've been wanting to call him, but for some reason I'm too scared to. Oh well, I'll get a hold of him sometime in the future...maybe. I miss him now...but I think I'm finally over him...idk...

Valentine's Day is coming up. BOOOOOOOOO! I hate V-day, I never have a valentine. I swear they made Valentine's and Sweetest Day to piss off and depress single people. Does anyone wanna be my VALENTINE??? :)

That's about all.
Peace out!

Gen

Yay it's the weekend, just finished up my first week of classes. They don't seem to be that bad, it should be pretty easy this semester. They are nicely spread out, 2 classes everyday. I bought my books...only spent $272, I was really surprised it didn't cost more since I had to buy multiple books and such for each of my classes.

At the beginnning of this week my mom was in the hospital for 3 days because she had an irregular heartbeat. They ran a bunch of test and made sure there were no blood clots and didn't find any problems. So then they took the paddles and shocked her heart back into a regular rhythm...that's kinda freaky. She's back at home now on meds, but doing good. She's still looking for a new job...what fun.

I'm really getting sick of this freezing weather and all the snow...we better have a snow day soon, everybody pray we do.

I'm out

<3 Gen

Why hello there, it's been awhile. Not much has gone on...break is quite boring. I guess I will recap some of the highlights of my holiday break so far...

- Christmas Eve we traditionally went to my aunt/uncle house, I got to see all of my cousins, it was great to see them again...it's been awhile. Christmas Day was pretty good, I spend it with the family. I picked out all of my presents so it was no surprise. I got: Season 8 of Friends, Butterfly Effect, True Star- Tommy Girl Perfume, a few hoodies from AE, cute socks from Gap, Gift cards for Best Buy, all kinds of candy, money...hmmm that might be everything. Ohhh yeahhh, Britt got me these really cute penguin pajamas! Anyway, we had dinner at our house with my aunt, uncle, and cuz. Then, later at night we went to my dad's side of the family (a.k.a. the crazy and loud people, geez you would be amazed how hyper these people are) I hadn't seen them in a really really long time so that was fun. I was talking to my aunt and uncle who just moved into a condo in Stow, when they told me where it was at I realized that they moved into the same condo cluster as Britt's mom...hahah they are next door neightbors, wow what a small world. 

- I got an unexpect interesting call from Tristan a few days after christmas. I haven't talked to him since last year after all the drama broke out. We played catch up and he apologized for everything that happened. I'm not sure how I feel about him and all the crap that happened....it really pissed me off. It was nice to hear from him again and know that he knows what a huge asshole he was to me, but also it was kinda awkward. I guess I can learn to forgive and forget...we'll see about that.

I bet it's gonna be the same way with Bob, I won't hear from him for a year. Then, he'll call me and try to pretend nothing ever happened, and that he never ignored me like right now. I never thought Tristan would call me, he's the last person I expected to hear from....Yet the only person I want to call me, hasn't and probably won't ever again. I haven't been able to bring myself to call Bob. Everytime I try to, I end up talking myself out of it. I sent him an email 2.5 weeks ago and I still haven't heard from him...Kristin tried to getting a hold of him too....I'm convinced he's in jail or dead, or just being an asshole who forgot what the last thing was that he told me before he said goodbye, "we're friends, and we'll talk once in a while to say hi and hang out or something..." riiiight, we haven't talked since. I'm done...

- My aunt (meaning my biological family) had a little get together the day before new years eve and had me over for dinner. It was great, I got to see my brother and niece and nephew...I think it was the best part of my break so far, I haven't seen them in a couple years. We are suppose to get together again before I go back to school...I can't wait.

- Kristin came up from Columbus for the week of Christmas/ New Years...we hung out a few times, nothing too exciting. We built a snow fort and went sledding in my backyard, and spend all night till the early morning playing my sister's GameCube that she got for christmas...omg I'm like addicted to it.

- New Years sucked, I didn't do anything because none of my friends were home. So I just chilled at home and relaxed...blah.

- Found out that Britt might not being coming back to the dorm this semester, that means I won't have a roommate....damn it *tear*
Pleeeease Britt don't leave me all alone.


OK, I'm sure you're bored with reading about my life....I sure am bored living it. I can't wait to go back to school, my family is sooooo annoying. Well back to my boring life...staying up till 4-5am, sleeping till 2pm, knitting, playing GameCube, and eating like craaaazy! Later!

Love ya bunches
Gen

I had a great weekend...

Kristin was home from Columbus so I spend almost all weekend with her. Saturday morning I got up and Kristin came to pick me up so we could go shopping. We went to Jo-ann's to buy yarn. I ran out of yarn for my blanket so I had to get more, and Kristin had to buy some so she could make scarfs for everyone as Christmas presents. I bought the same color that I had been using, but when I started knitting with it I noticed that it was a tad different shade. Now why wouldn't they make the color the same everytime?...oh well, I'll make do. Friday night she was suppose to come over but her headlights wouldn't work, so after shopping on Saturday we took her car into the service place. They ended up being burned out...kinda weird that they would burn out at the exact same time. Then, we came back to school and got lunch and watched Mean Girls. Kristin left to go home so she could go out to dinner with her mom.

Kristin came over later that night. Britt got home from work. And I was just sitting around knitting. Delta Chi was having a party, nothing big just a little party for all the initiated guys. We decided to go over there and hang out with Paul. We all got pretty wasted...Thank god it's about time I got drunk there...and period, it's been awhile. We all had a good time being stupid, Britt and Kristin left Bob a few drunken messages on his machine...oops! I broke down whining and almost crying about Bob to Kristin and all these other random people there, I looked like a lunitic. Kristin understood it all since she knew things were over between Bob and I before I even knew...ridiculous. It's not my fault I miss him so much, I know I should just forget about him, but it's easier said than done. Ya know? Britt and Paul left early like 2:30-3am and drove Kristin's car back to the dorm and went to sleep. Kristin and I hung out at the frat till 4am then walked our drunk asses back home. Got some food from Rosies and then went to bed around 6am...unfortunately we both had to get up at 9am because Kristin had to go home so she could leave for Pittsburgh at 10am and I had to meet my group to work on a math project at 10 also. I was soooooooo freakin tired. Luckily the project didn't take very long, I came back and crashed until dinnertime. 

I had a great night, I'm glad Kristin did too...since most of Kent is pretty boring (compared to OSU.) Don't worry Kristin, we'll be down to visit you sooner or later.

Well I'm gonna go knit before bed...night everyone!

Love, Gen....a.k.a. My Little Tomato (Britt's drunken nickname for me, everyone at the party was calling me that.)

Last week I went home on Tuesday for Thanksgiving break, since my one class on Wednesday was cancelled thankfully! It was really nice to be home even though my dad and sister both told me to just go back to school because they didn't want me at home...thanks, I feel loved. Anyway, I spent Tuesday night writing my Geography paper so I could e-mail it to my prof before Wednesday at noon. By the way, I ended up getting an A on it.

Wednesday morning I had a dentist appointment...boy do I love it when people pick at my teeth. They said that I've got a cavity so I have an appointment to get it filled at the beginning of x-mas break, also over x-mas break I am suppose to get my wisdom teeth out since at the end of December I won't have dental insurance anymore...we'll see if I actually get them out. So, this x-mas break seems like it is going to be a painful one! Hahaha! Bob sent me an e-mail after work on Wednesday to say Happy Thanksgiving and that he's been really really busy and isn't avoiding me intentionally. I was really surprised to hear from him, well atleast he took the time out of his busy schedule to contact me in some way. I really miss him alot, but when I read the e-mail I got this feeling of not caring at all...I don't know. I hope to see him sometime over x-mas break either going out or at work.

For Thanksgiving I went to my cousin Kevin's, always a fun time had by all. A little bit of x-mas was thrown in to Turkey Day, Kevin burned me the new DMX CD and the new Chingy CD...thanks Kev. My aunt cooked an absolutely delicious dinner, it was a nice change from campus food...ewwww! Campus food makes me sick to my stomach, literally. Dinner went well then less than a minutes after we were done eating all the kids (no including myself, im not a kid, im 20 yrs old) ran off to play with Kevin but instead got into trouble for trying to kick his ass, and they all wound up in time-out. Hahaha, what a perfect dessert! It was really great to see my extended family, especially because half of them will be out of town for x-mas.

Friday I spent cleaning out/ taking apart all the furniture in my sister's bedroom to be thrown away. My mom rewarded me by taking to the movies...to see a movie that she wanted to see, hmmmm. We went to see Shall We Dance with Richard Gere and J-Lo, now that is an interesting pair...also Vince from Will and Grace was in to. It was an alright movie.

Saturday was x-mas shopping day so we could miss some of the crowd. I picked out all my gifts for my parents to give me so it kinda sucks that I know everything I'm getting for x-mas, oh well I'll survive. I got some of my shopping done for friends and family, but I'm stumped with what to get my Dad and sister...they refuse to tell me what they want. I hate when people do that.

A week and a half left of classes, a week of finals, then its home for a month for x-mas and new years! Yay! Hopefully I will be able to get a couple of hours in at work, that is if they need me.

17 days left...

It's beddy bye time...

Love, Gen

Let's see what's been happening...

Last saturday (Nov. 13th) was my B-day. Wooohooo the big 20. Yeah right, it sucks getting old, it was no biggie. I totally could have skipped my B-day and I wouldn't have cared, when I woke up in the morning I forgot it was my B-day...that's pretty sad. My family took me out to dinner at the Olive Garden and Britt came along with us...it was yummy! Then, my mom, sister, and I went to see The Polar Express. It was a pretty good movie, kinda freaky in a way, but good! Thanks to everybody who remembered my B-day, and those who didn't...you suck (I'll be expecting a belated happy birthday from you). I got Mean Girls and Season 6 of Friends on DVD, and a couple little things from Britt. Thanks!

My life has been pretty boring...I've seriously basically just sat around doing nothing in the dorm for the past month. I wish I had something to keep me busy. Blah, blah, blah....hmmmmmm.....

Classes are excellent, except for math. I hate that class, it's such a waste of time. Oh well, you'll have that. Hehehehe I love saying that, I miss listening to everybody use that phrase last year.

I miss Bob soooo much, I can't believe how hard I'm taking this. I wrote him a letter telling him about how I feel about everything between us, I dropped it off at work a week ago. We talk for a little bit, but it was really awkward. Things seemed really different with us. Like being friends wasn't an option and wouldn't work...I don't know. I still haven't heard from him with a response to my letter. Oh well whatever. I'm just tired of trying, and I don't understand how he has changed so much in such a short time.

I've got two days of classes this week. Tuesday afternoon I'm going home for Thanksgiving. Yay! I'm pretty excited to see my family, I'm getting kinda sick of being at school all the time. Blah, blah, blah....

That's about it, my life is boring and sucks, and nobody loves me anymore. 

Leave something good guys.

Love, Gen

Happy Halloween and Happy Birthday Dad! :)

I'm wondering if anybody reads this anymore or if I'm wasting my time writing in here? Anyway...

Last week Bob broke up with me *tear* I'm pretty hurt and upset about it. I really didn't want it to be over between us. I guess we are gonna be "friends" according to him, which means I won't see or talk to him ever again...I'm not liking that idea at all, but what can I do??...Don't worry, I think I have a plan. I'm not gonna get into any details about the break up right now mainly because I am too lazy to write it all out, but if you want to know what's going on or what happened you can ask me. 

Last night I was at home to celebrate my Dad's birthday. We went out to dinner at Applebees, yummmm. Chicken Quesadillas rock my world!! I was sitting at the table putting sugar in my iced tea when our waitress came over, I wasn't paying any attention while she took the rest of the fam's orders, but when I looked up as she took my order I realized that it was one of my friends from H.S., Danielle Panzero...wow I haven't seen her since before graduation. We talked for a few about school and stuff, she was planning on going to Kent, but is commuting to University of Akron instead. It was great to actually see someone who a graduated with, it's been awhile. After dinner, I went over Ashley's house to hang out with her family for awhile...I love them SOOOOOO much! Ashley and Andy were chillin and carving pumpkins. All I can say is, Pumpkins and Soft Scrub are an amazing combination. HAHAHAHAHA!! 

Today I had to get up early to help my Dad, and step-bro cut down/ cut up an enormous tree that broke in half early in the summer during a storm. Wow...talk about "worst home videos of cutting down trees", we need Tree Cutting and Safety 101, Hahaha! First of all we had a rope tied to the tree so we could guide and pull it down as they cut it. That didn't work out to well, they didn't cut it right and the tree ended up going the opposite direction than we intended and almost landed on my mom who was standing on the other side where she thought she was safe...luckily she got out of the way just in the nick of time. After we got the huge tree down on the ground and started cutting off the branches the chainsaw got stuck in one of the knots in the tree. We rolled the tree over so it would relieve some of the pressure from the branch so we could pull the saw out. As we did that the branch that was supporting the tree up off the ground snapped and sent the chainsaw flying out of the tree and through the air, landing 2 feet away from me. Geez, 2 family member almost killed just because my dad felt the need to play with a tree. Hahaha, it's all good, it was worth seeing all the stuff happen.

Ok, well that's all for now.
I'm out like a chainsaw from a tree....hahaha! I know, that was gay! Atleast I try.

Love ya, Gen
